I can't tell Cuz what happened.

286
00:22:40,155 --> 00:22:43,116
Because he'll find out
I drove by myself.

287
00:22:44,075 --> 00:22:45,075
I'm dead.

288
00:22:46,273 --> 00:22:48,359
Maybe we should ask her
when she's okay.

289
00:22:48,589 --> 00:22:50,383
- Okay.
- She might still be stressed.

290
00:22:51,974 --> 00:22:53,308
Uh, Aemie girl.

291
00:22:53,710 --> 00:22:55,003
Can I talk to you in private?

292
00:22:57,088 --> 00:22:58,798
This is a private room.

293
00:22:59,065 --> 00:23:01,509
No. I mean, like,
just the two of us.

294
00:23:01,679 --> 00:23:02,679
Oh.

295
00:23:07,046 --> 00:23:08,214
This is so good.

296
00:23:09,517 --> 00:23:10,643
Excuse me for a sec.

297
00:23:14,981 --> 00:23:16,775
You know Kevin
and I are over, right?

298
00:23:17,950 --> 00:23:20,379
It's been a week
or two, I think.

299
00:23:26,159 --> 00:23:27,249
Venice.

300
00:23:27,719 --> 00:23:28,720
Sorry.

301
00:23:28,745 --> 00:23:32,040
I just don't know
any comforting lines.

302
00:23:33,584 --> 00:23:34,626
Why did you two break up?

303
00:23:38,348 --> 00:23:41,017
I found out that Kevin is
a member of the mafia.

304
00:23:43,635 --> 00:23:44,635
Oh.

305
00:23:44,803 --> 00:23:47,097
Well, good thing you
broke up with him.

306
00:23:47,097 --> 00:23:50,183
- No.
- I know all that mafia stuff is bad.

307
00:23:50,308 --> 00:23:51,620
No, no, no.

308
00:23:51,994 --> 00:23:53,996
We all know Kevin
isn't a bad person.

309
00:23:55,271 --> 00:23:57,690
There's only two reasons why
someone would join the mafia.

310
00:23:57,982 --> 00:23:59,943
One, it's a personal choice.

311
00:24:00,068 --> 00:24:02,504
Two, you don't have
any other choice.

312
00:24:02,604 --> 00:24:04,606
Sometimes, there's
also the case where

313
00:24:04,631 --> 00:24:07,717
they end up in it because
they're the child of a mafia boss.

314
00:24:08,118 --> 00:24:09,118
Why?

315
00:24:09,953 --> 00:24:11,621
Is Kevin the son
of a mafia boss?

316
00:24:12,497 --> 00:24:13,748
I don't know, really.

317
00:24:14,415 --> 00:24:17,585
But the truth is, he's the
one who broke up with me.

318
00:24:18,378 --> 00:24:21,729
Aemie, girl. I swear, I have no
problem with him being in the mafia.

319
00:24:23,508 --> 00:24:24,508
You know.

320
00:24:25,282 --> 00:24:26,825
If Zeke was the same,

321
00:24:28,471 --> 00:24:30,098
I wouldn't know
what to do either.

322
00:24:31,141 --> 00:24:32,934
You really love
your husband, huh?

323
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:40,222
I love him so much?

324
00:24:41,985 --> 00:24:43,403
How do you know that?

325
00:24:57,709 --> 00:24:59,544
Am I falling in love with Zeke?

326
00:25:01,004 --> 00:25:02,672
How am I supposed to know?

327
00:25:18,696 --> 00:25:19,696
Oh.

328
00:25:20,781 --> 00:25:21,781
Uh, miss.

329
00:25:22,317 --> 00:25:24,777
I think you walked
into the wrong room.

330
00:25:25,737 --> 00:25:26,737
No.

331
00:25:27,197 --> 00:25:28,364
I'm in the right room.

332
00:25:30,116 --> 00:25:31,492
I'm Fiona Stonehurst.

333
00:25:32,118 --> 00:25:34,412
Ezekiel's girlfriend.

334
00:25:39,209 --> 00:25:40,209
Wait.

335
00:25:42,212 --> 00:25:44,339
Are you the hospital janitress?

336
00:25:46,132 --> 00:25:47,397
Perfect timing.

337
00:25:47,425 --> 00:25:49,594
Could you clean the restroom?

338
00:25:49,903 --> 00:25:52,197
I'm a bit particular
about cleanliness.

339
00:25:52,222 --> 00:25:54,682
So, I'd really appreciate it.

340
00:25:58,394 --> 00:25:59,437
What did she say she was?

341
00:25:59,687 --> 00:26:00,813
Girlfriend?

342
00:26:02,357 --> 00:26:04,567
And she's even holding his hand.

343
00:26:06,110 --> 00:26:07,695
I'm not losing this one.

344
00:26:08,571 --> 00:26:10,031
I'm the perfect wife.

345
00:26:10,817 --> 00:26:12,861
And according to
rule number seven,

346
00:26:13,743 --> 00:26:16,871
don't let other girls
come near him.

347
00:26:19,666 --> 00:26:21,292
How do I get rid of her?

348
00:26:23,544 --> 00:26:24,544
What if...

349
00:26:25,713 --> 00:26:27,507
what if I scare her off?

350
00:26:30,843 --> 00:26:32,637
You shameless woman!

351
00:26:33,304 --> 00:26:35,682
You've got some nerve
getting close to my husband!

352
00:26:35,932 --> 00:26:37,642
Then I'll drag her.

353
00:26:38,017 --> 00:26:39,851
Get over here. Get over here!

354
00:26:40,954 --> 00:26:42,330
Then I'll give her a bath!

355
00:26:42,355 --> 00:26:43,355
Oh my God!

356
00:26:49,404 --> 00:26:50,404
Take this!

357
00:26:51,322 --> 00:26:53,491
Okay! Straight ahead.

358
00:26:53,586 --> 00:26:55,451
Just keep going straight!
Just keep going straight!

359
00:26:55,476 --> 00:26:56,953
Until you crash into something.

360
00:26:56,978 --> 00:26:59,647
U-turn, U-turn, U-turn!

361
00:26:59,904 --> 00:27:01,822
Left!

362
00:27:01,916 --> 00:27:03,293
Oops, straight ahead!

363
00:27:03,293 --> 00:27:05,169
Dead end!

364
00:27:05,253 --> 00:27:07,547
Right!

365
00:27:07,730 --> 00:27:08,898
Right!

366
00:27:08,923 --> 00:27:10,800
Oops, oops! Straight ahead!

367
00:27:11,050 --> 00:27:13,219
Maybe that'll make her leave.

368
00:27:13,720 --> 00:27:14,720
Okay!

369
00:27:14,762 --> 00:27:16,055
There, there, there!
Get out already!

370
00:27:16,055 --> 00:27:17,668
Go, go, go!

371
00:27:18,993 --> 00:27:20,811
Come on, straight ahead!
Just keep going straight!

372
00:27:20,838 --> 00:27:22,423
You can do it!

373
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:27,793
Don't ever show
your face here again!

374
00:27:27,818 --> 00:27:29,278
Don't come back here!

375
00:27:31,103 --> 00:27:32,146
Understand?

376
00:27:35,992 --> 00:27:37,577
Eyy!

377
00:27:38,494 --> 00:27:40,184
Um, excuse me!

378
00:27:40,923 --> 00:27:41,923
Janitress?

379
00:27:42,785 --> 00:27:44,537
Aren't you gonna clean
the comfort room now?

380
00:27:46,628 --> 00:27:49,088
Hmm, no.

381
00:27:50,548 --> 00:27:54,427
I prefer to start cleaning this.

382
00:27:57,221 --> 00:27:59,474
Ouch! Oh my effing god!

383
