414
00:29:38,322 --> 00:29:41,534
Okay, well, I've known
Ezekiel ever since college.

415
00:29:42,118 --> 00:29:44,370
So I practically know
everything about him.

416
00:29:50,460 --> 00:29:55,131
Anyway, Aemie, I think
it's time you get some rest.

417
00:29:55,673 --> 00:29:56,673
You look...

418
00:29:57,550 --> 00:29:58,968
you look so tired.

419
00:30:00,052 --> 00:30:01,679
But don't worry about Ezekiel.

420
00:30:02,513 --> 00:30:03,973
I'll take care of him.

421
00:30:05,850 --> 00:30:06,850
No,

422
00:30:07,268 --> 00:30:12,148
I'm completely capable of
taking care of my husband.

423
00:30:21,106 --> 00:30:22,106
Oh no!

424
00:30:22,742 --> 00:30:23,993
She's still here!

425
00:30:24,018 --> 00:30:25,363
She won't leave!

426
00:30:26,162 --> 00:30:28,164
Maybe I should
just say it directly.

427
00:30:28,331 --> 00:30:29,457
So she'll get it.

428
00:30:53,272 --> 00:30:54,272
I love him.

429
00:30:55,441 --> 00:30:57,401
And I always will.

430
00:31:18,388 --> 00:31:20,000
She said I'm a Janitress...

431
00:31:34,055 --> 00:31:35,198
We can use that route.

432
00:31:35,230 --> 00:31:37,185
- Yeah, definitely.
- And that car.

433
00:31:37,333 --> 00:31:39,752
So this is the whole entire
map of the Grand Park Hotel.

434
00:31:39,777 --> 00:31:40,777
Mm-hmm.

435
00:31:41,028 --> 00:31:42,947
So we're gonna layout this map.

436
00:31:43,030 --> 00:31:44,030
Mm-hmm.

437
00:31:44,652 --> 00:31:46,117
And assemble our targets.

438
00:31:46,951 --> 00:31:47,951
Meisha!

439
00:31:48,690 --> 00:31:52,694
So you're the one who ordered
those idiots to follow Roswell to Hawaii?

440
00:31:52,826 --> 00:31:55,065
- Huh?
- Yeah. And?

441
00:31:55,293 --> 00:31:56,544
Fuck you, Meisha!

442
00:31:56,836 --> 00:31:58,522
Fiona got dragged into it too!

443
00:32:04,206 --> 00:32:05,749
I didn't tell them to hurt her.

444
00:32:06,554 --> 00:32:09,390
But also, I don't really care.

445
00:32:09,932 --> 00:32:14,195
We may be friends, but
don't you ever cross the line.

446
00:32:14,421 --> 00:32:17,793
You wouldn't wanna
see what we're capable of.

447
00:32:19,082 --> 00:32:20,291
Well, fuck you too.

448
00:32:20,731 --> 00:32:23,280
Then why don't you just
kill Roswell's wife instead?

449
00:32:23,527 --> 00:32:24,540
Huh?

450
00:32:24,565 --> 00:32:27,276
We're just following
orders from our boss.

451
00:32:27,950 --> 00:32:30,828
And also, Fiona is still alive.

452
00:32:31,746 --> 00:32:32,997
You're being so dramatic!

453
00:32:33,706 --> 00:32:38,628
Besides, wasn't Blood supposed
to be handling Roswell's wife?

454
00:32:38,858 --> 00:32:42,227
You know what happened to me
the last time I was there, right?

455
00:33:57,081 --> 00:33:58,748
Oh no! Hey, Zeke!

456
00:33:59,042 --> 00:34:00,574
Oh no, Zeke! Hey!

457
00:34:00,826 --> 00:34:01,869
What happened?

458
00:34:01,894 --> 00:34:03,226
Easy, easy.

459
00:34:04,837 --> 00:34:06,602
Why did you stand up?

460
00:34:06,627 --> 00:34:07,711
Are you okay?

461
00:34:07,736 --> 00:34:09,213
- I'm fucking useless.
- You should've just called--

462
00:34:09,238 --> 00:34:10,990
Called me.

463
00:34:11,350 --> 00:34:13,227
I was going to
get you breakfast.

464
00:34:20,942 --> 00:34:22,652
How many hours was I out?

465
00:34:24,111 --> 00:34:25,111
Hours?

466
00:34:25,693 --> 00:34:28,112
Oh my god, Dong, you've
been asleep for days.

467
00:34:28,548 --> 00:34:30,590
You've probably had a
ton of dreams by now.

468
00:34:31,073 --> 00:34:34,452
Meanwhile, I've been
worried sick about you.

469
00:34:38,998 --> 00:34:40,570
What happened to you?

470
00:34:41,178 --> 00:34:42,518
Good luck on your exams.

471
00:34:42,543 --> 00:34:44,003
You're so pale.

472
00:34:44,028 --> 00:34:45,521
You don't look okay.

473
00:34:45,546 --> 00:34:48,716
I'm not leaving until you tell
me why you're acting like this.

474
00:34:48,829 --> 00:34:49,830
Zeke!

475
00:34:49,884 --> 00:34:52,219
Zeke! Why is there
so much blood?

476
00:34:52,244 --> 00:34:53,244
Help!

477
00:34:53,554 --> 00:34:54,805
Please, help!

478
00:34:54,930 --> 00:34:56,323
Help!

479
00:34:56,348 --> 00:34:57,856
Please, stay with me!

480
00:34:57,881 --> 00:34:59,007
Stay with me, Zeke!

481
00:34:59,057 --> 00:35:00,057
Stay with me!

482
00:35:00,120 --> 00:35:01,120
Aemie.

483
00:35:01,645 --> 00:35:04,064
Please, I don't know what to do!

484
00:35:04,064 --> 00:35:05,733
Don't leave me, please!

485
00:35:06,734 --> 00:35:08,402
Don't leave me!

486
00:35:09,236 --> 00:35:10,863
Don't leave me!

487
00:35:17,388 --> 00:35:18,640
Thank you, wife.

488
00:35:28,665 --> 00:35:31,360
I really thought I
was going to lose you.

489
00:35:33,511 --> 00:35:34,888
I'm never gonna leave you.

490
00:35:36,680 --> 00:35:37,848
Unless you want me to.

491
00:35:37,873 --> 00:35:40,751
Zeke! I don't!

492
00:35:54,151 --> 00:35:55,611
You look like hell, wife.

493
00:35:58,268 --> 00:35:59,268
Because...

494
00:36:00,721 --> 00:36:03,349
I took melatonin and
coffee at the same time!

495
00:36:03,374 --> 00:36:05,334
I think they're
fighting each other!

496
00:36:07,985 --> 00:36:09,814
You should have woken up early.

497
00:36:09,839 --> 00:36:12,132
So I could sleep properly

498
00:36:13,050 --> 00:36:14,593
You should really
look at yourself.

499
00:36:18,556 --> 00:36:19,556
Ah!

500
00:36:23,225 --> 00:36:24,225
Hey!

501
00:36:24,611 --> 00:36:27,572
You didn't even change
clothes, or take a bath?

502
00:36:30,956 --> 00:36:31,956
The audacity?

503
00:36:32,220 --> 00:36:33,472
Look who's talking.

504
00:36:33,497 --> 00:36:34,812
You haven't showered either.

505
00:36:35,034 --> 00:36:36,034
We're even.

506
00:36:38,117 --> 00:36:39,410
I'm gonna go change clothes.

507
00:36:41,370 --> 00:36:43,330
Wait, I'm just gonna
change clothes, okay?

508
00:36:46,487 --> 00:36:47,501
Stay right there!

509
00:36:47,501 --> 00:36:48,752
Don't stand up again!

510
00:37:22,870 --> 00:37:23,870
Aemie.

511
00:37:24,204 --> 00:37:25,456
Aemie Roswell.

512
00:37:25,998 --> 00:37:27,374
Excuse me, ma'am.

513
00:37:27,666 --> 00:37:29,764
Do you have an
appointment with the CEO?

514
00:37:30,419 --> 00:37:31,419
Actually, no.

515
00:37:31,495 --> 00:37:34,247
I'm just checking
Ezekiel's office because

516
00:37:34,381 --> 00:37:36,592
I'll be managing it while
he's still in the hospital.

517
00:37:36,884 --> 00:37:38,552
And you are?

518
00:37:38,761 --> 00:37:39,761
Fiona.

519
00:37:39,970 --> 00:37:41,176
Fiona Stonehurst.

520
00:37:41,805 --> 00:37:43,098
Ezekiel's girlfriend.

521
00:37:47,937 --> 00:37:53,648
Anyway, I think we need
to remove all of this trash.

522
00:37:53,901 --> 00:37:55,235
It looks awful, doesn't it?

523
00:37:55,495 --> 00:37:56,503
Look!

524
00:37:56,528 --> 00:37:57,528
Yuck!

525
00:37:58,739 --> 00:38:00,032
Don't worry about Ezekiel.

526
00:38:00,366 --> 00:38:01,966
I'll just talk to him
when he comes back.

527
00:38:02,576 --> 00:38:05,371
And for the meantime, I'll
take care of everything here.

528
00:38:05,871 --> 00:38:07,498
I'm gonna renovate this place.

529
00:38:07,831 --> 00:38:11,502
Uh, Ms. Fiona, maybe I
should call Mr. Roswell first?

530
00:38:12,711 --> 00:38:13,711
Like I said,

531
00:38:14,505 --> 00:38:15,825
I'll take care of
everything here.

532
00:38:19,035 --> 00:38:20,035
Oh no!

533
00:38:20,153 --> 00:38:21,545
Not another crazy one.

534
00:38:23,472 --> 00:38:24,472
Hello?

535
00:38:25,474 --> 00:38:26,474
Yes.

536
00:38:26,892 --> 00:38:31,814
We need to do some
major, major renovations.

537
00:38:39,570 --> 00:38:41,572
Sorry, what was your name again?

538
00:38:42,157 --> 00:38:43,157
Kate.

539
00:38:43,216 --> 00:38:44,217
Kate Alonzo.

540
00:38:44,242 --> 00:38:45,242
Okay.

541
00:38:45,482 --> 00:38:46,482
Thanks, Kate.

542
00:39:01,396 --> 00:39:02,898
Hey, easy!

543
00:39:05,305 --> 00:39:06,889
- Fuck!
- Easy.

544
00:39:07,387 --> 00:39:08,387
You're so stubborn!

545
00:39:09,148 --> 00:39:12,127
The doctor already
told you to get some rest.

546
00:39:14,055 --> 00:39:15,055
Wait, wait.

547
00:39:16,721 --> 00:39:17,721
You two,

548
00:39:19,017 --> 00:39:20,602
who taught Aemie how to drive?

549
00:39:23,249 --> 00:39:24,249
Answer me!

550
00:39:25,576 --> 00:39:27,181
I don't know, boss.

551
00:39:28,236 --> 00:39:31,015
Maybe it was, uh, Lamperouge.

552
00:39:31,040 --> 00:39:32,931
Maybe he gave
her driving lessons.

553
00:39:33,624 --> 00:39:35,787
Ah, Zeke,

554
00:39:36,119 --> 00:39:38,538
a bald guy taught me
how to drive.

555
00:39:39,086 --> 00:39:40,086
Bald?

556
00:39:41,111 --> 00:39:42,295
Dominic.

557
00:39:43,932 --> 00:39:44,932
Don't you know him?

558
00:39:45,063 --> 00:39:46,538
He already has a family.

559
00:39:46,718 --> 00:39:48,223
I wanna meet that asshole.

560
00:39:50,585 --> 00:39:51,585
Okay.

561
00:39:54,824 --> 00:39:57,494
I'm going to ask you
assholes a few questions.

562
00:39:58,944 --> 00:40:00,279
How you answer them

563
00:40:01,662 --> 00:40:04,999
will determine in what state
you'll be leaving this place.

564
00:40:08,621 --> 00:40:09,664
It's either

565
00:40:10,354 --> 00:40:11,897
you're going to be running,

566
00:40:13,425 --> 00:40:15,469
or you'll be thrown
out as corpses.

567
00:40:19,543 --> 00:40:20,753
The choice is yours.

568
00:40:25,073 --> 00:40:26,073
Now tell me,

569
00:40:28,775 --> 00:40:29,901
do you have families?

570
00:40:37,309 --> 00:40:38,352
I'll assume you do.

571
00:40:39,085 --> 00:40:40,419
You still wanna see them?

572
00:40:40,949 --> 00:40:41,949
Yeah?

573
00:40:43,893 --> 00:40:44,894
Then you better talk.

574
00:40:49,662 --> 00:40:51,100
You should be thankful

575
00:40:52,053 --> 00:40:54,168
that nothing
happened to my wife.

576
00:40:54,873 --> 00:40:57,325
Because if she was
hurt in any other way,

577
00:40:57,960 --> 00:41:00,712
I wouldn't even be giving
this chance for you guys to talk.

578
00:41:01,843 --> 00:41:02,843
Now tell me,

579
00:41:03,507 --> 00:41:05,425
who sent you after us?

580
00:41:06,009 --> 00:41:07,427
Fuck you, Roswell.

581
00:41:07,719 --> 00:41:10,141
Your father is the reason we
don't have families anymore!

582
00:41:10,639 --> 00:41:12,182
Even if you kill us,

583
00:41:12,724 --> 00:41:14,351
you're still going to die!

584
00:41:14,726 --> 00:41:16,103
Your wife too!

585
00:41:16,854 --> 00:41:18,939
The Yaji will never
stop coming after you.

586
00:41:19,357 --> 00:41:20,691
Wrong choice of words.

587
00:41:51,638 --> 00:41:52,638
I love him.

588
00:41:53,765 --> 00:41:55,642
And I always will.

589
00:42:00,439 --> 00:42:01,481
You know, guys.

590
00:42:02,762 --> 00:42:04,806
She's really not
gonna let me sleep.

591
00:42:05,903 --> 00:42:06,903
What exactly...

592
00:42:07,756 --> 00:42:09,716
What exactly is this
thing she's calling love?

593
00:42:11,450 --> 00:42:12,784
How do you know...

594
00:42:13,700 --> 00:42:16,662
How do you know when
you're in love with someone?

595
00:42:18,207 --> 00:42:20,083
Can I use a
call-a-friend this time?

596
00:42:20,626 --> 00:42:21,626
Hmm?

597
00:42:28,508 --> 00:42:29,508
Oh.

598
00:42:32,763 --> 00:42:34,513
Hello, cuz. What's up?

599
00:42:35,474 --> 00:42:36,634
What does being in love mean?

600
00:42:37,809 --> 00:42:38,809
And...

601
00:42:39,102 --> 00:42:41,104
How do you know when...

602
00:42:42,482 --> 00:42:44,677
you really, truly love someone?

603
00:42:46,421 --> 00:42:47,711
Oh, cuz.

604
00:42:47,736 --> 00:42:49,112
You came to the right person.

605
00:42:49,137 --> 00:42:50,817
I'm practically a
certified expert on that.

606
00:42:50,864 --> 00:42:51,876
Okay, listen.

607
00:42:52,010 --> 00:42:55,097
I'll tell you the signs
that you're in love, okay?

608
00:42:55,953 --> 00:42:57,496
Okay, okay!

609
00:43:01,083 --> 00:43:02,542
Oh, hubby.

610
00:43:02,709 --> 00:43:03,709
Have you eaten yet?

611
00:43:03,919 --> 00:43:04,919
Not yet.

612
00:43:07,631 --> 00:43:08,631
Oh, wow.

613
00:43:08,966 --> 00:43:09,966
You cooked.

614
00:43:21,311 --> 00:43:22,479
Here is the first sign.

615
00:43:22,504 --> 00:43:24,131
When you feel something different,

616
00:43:24,156 --> 00:43:25,783
if he's gonna come near and touch you...

617
00:43:31,142 --> 00:43:32,142
It means...

618
00:43:32,612 --> 00:43:33,612
You're in love.

619
00:43:50,881 --> 00:43:52,699
Zeke. Zeke, wait.

620
00:43:53,458 --> 00:43:54,458
What's the matter?

621
00:43:55,305 --> 00:43:56,347
You don't want to ride a car?

622
00:43:56,372 --> 00:43:59,527
What if what happened
last time happens again?

623
00:44:01,844 --> 00:44:05,222
Were you the one who stole
the one hundred million pesos?

624
00:44:05,247 --> 00:44:06,374
I will not answer that!

625
00:44:06,456 --> 00:44:07,666
This is harassment.

626
00:44:07,691 --> 00:44:09,569
I agree with the CFO.

627
00:44:10,375 --> 00:44:12,988
You cannot ask such questions
in front of the entire board.

628
00:44:13,013 --> 00:44:14,013
That's...

629
00:44:14,704 --> 00:44:15,887
that's unprofessional.

630
00:44:18,196 --> 00:44:19,223
You're not needed here.

631
00:44:19,248 --> 00:44:21,959
This meeting is
about the toy industry.

632
00:44:22,388 --> 00:44:24,616
Which I'm helping
your wife with, Ezekiel.

633
00:44:24,641 --> 00:44:26,685
Oh, so she's actually
going to help me.

634
00:44:26,710 --> 00:44:28,195
Why isn't it pink anymore?

635
00:44:28,295 --> 00:44:29,921
I threw out all of your trash!

636
00:44:30,660 --> 00:44:32,527
I wanted it to make
it a little more...

637
00:44:32,966 --> 00:44:33,550
professional?

638
00:44:33,550 --> 00:44:34,563
I think you should

639
00:44:34,588 --> 00:44:36,243
take a look at this
for consideration.

640
00:44:38,001 --> 00:44:39,978
Good thing you stopped by again!

641
00:44:40,165 --> 00:44:41,332
Good afternoon, ma'am.

642
00:44:41,383 --> 00:44:43,469
We'll help you and
Dong sell these.

643
00:44:43,494 --> 00:44:44,745
Really? Is that okay?

644
00:44:44,770 --> 00:44:45,770
Of course!

645
00:44:47,022 --> 00:44:49,566
You'll be dead soon.

646
00:44:49,566 --> 00:44:51,109
Aemie Roswell.
